# Strings

## Use single quotes

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
const name = 'John';

// ❌ BAD
const name = "John";
```

## Template literals for interpolation

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
const message = `Hello, ${name}!`;
const url = `${baseUrl}/users/${userId}`;

// ❌ BAD - string concatenation
const message = 'Hello, ' + name + '!';
const url = baseUrl + '/users/' + userId;
```

## Template literals for multiline

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
const html = `
  <div>
    <h1>${title}</h1>
  </div>
`;

// ❌ BAD
const html = '<div>\n' +
  '  <h1>' + title + '</h1>\n' +
  '</div>';
```

## Never use eval()

```typescript
// ❌ NEVER
eval('doSomething()');
new Function('return this');
```
